message: Hello future crafter! To get 100 points, always aim to combine a mundane liquid *extract* with a magical liquid *filtered* item. Use the vial on a solid mundane ingredient (e.g., dandelion, mushroom, amber) to create a mundane extract (30 points). Use the filter on a magical gas ingredient (e.g., ghostly vapor, dragon's breath) to create a magical filtered liquid (30 points). Combining these two will give you 100 points! Avoid using the vial on liquids, and avoid using the filter on solids, as these often lead to negative values. Filtering mundane gases also works (30 points) but yields a mundane filtered liquid, which combines with magical liquids for 70 points. Good luck!

The 'vial' tool is your primary way to get liquid 'extracts' from solid ingredients. If you need a mundane liquid and only have gas ingredients, the 'filter' tool can produce a 'filtered' liquid that works just as well. Avoid overly complex combinations; simplicity (one magical + one mundane) is key to max value!

message: Hey future crafter! Here's what I learned: Always use the 'vial' on 'solid' ingredients first; they reliably give +30 'extracts'. The ultimate goal for 100 points is to combine *one magical extract* with *one mundane extract*. Combining two mundane extracts gives 60 points. Avoid using the vial or filter on 'gas' ingredients, as they tend to yield negative results. Also, 'don't get too complicated' â€“ combining more than two items often leads to 'overcomplicated' items with reduced value. Steer clear of 'kraken ink' and generally avoid the 'filter' tool unless you have no other options or a very specific 'fume' that needs filtering.

message: Focus on extracting solid ingredients with the vial. Magical solids like 'dragon scale' and 'mandrake root' are great. Mundane solids like 'mushroom', 'bat wing', 'amber', and 'dandelion' are also reliable. Once you have two good extracts (one magical solid, one mundane solid), combine them to get a 100-point elixir! Avoid extracting liquids or gases, they tend to 'botch'. Also, don't filter 'botched' items, it makes them worse, and don't get 'too complicated' by mixing too many items. The 'mandrake-amber elixir' is a guaranteed 100 if you extract both successfully!
